title.narrative: Nutrition service providers have strengthened capacities to deliver Early Childhood Nutrition services, especially in priority regions

description.narrative: The 2019 Mid-Term-Review of the National Multisectoral Nutrition Action Plan (NMNAP) showed that increased utilization of infant and young child feeding (IYCF) services especially in UNICEF focus regions and Zanzibar from 5% in 2015, to 60% in 2018 and to 72% in 2019, contributed to a significant increase in the percentage of children receiving minimum acceptable diet from 20% in 2014 to 30% in 2018 nationally, which in turn contributed to the reduction in the prevalence of stunting and wasting among children under five years, respectively from 35% and 0.9% in 2014 to 32% and 0.4% in 2018, nationally. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
